cluding participant observation as both performer and spectator and interviews with legendary burlesquers and strippers, to share this remarkable story.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil rights movementszCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aGay liberation movementzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aLesbian activistsxCivil rightszCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex industryzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex workersxCivil rightszCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen entertainersxCivil rightszCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 7aART / Performance.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520398962?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520398962423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520398962/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles